The paper proposes a deep learning-based methodology for tuberculosis detection using microscopy images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep neural networks also falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the economic impact of tuberculosis and the need for a high-sensitivity diagnosis mechanism, which could potentially fall under the medical informatics (cs.MED) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
